The Proposal: -
Mavalgaon Kolhapur Method Dam No. 01, Latur under Godavari Irrigation Development Corporation
It is located on the Manar River in the Manar subdivision of the district near Mavalgaon village through the ZP division, Latur.
Built in 1995-96. The total length of the dam is 61.50 m. As such, the dam has 19 pillars and 20 ghatas. The total number of gates is 164 and the width of the gates is 2. 00 X 0. 50 m.
The water storage is 0.28 L.H.M. and the irrigation area is 71. That's so much.
The dam is in a bad state due to lack of maintenance and repair, and the dam does not hold water, thus 71.
It is not possible to water the irrigated area.
The Government has decided to convert the Mavalgaon-1 Co. P. system dam into a barrage under expansion and improvement.

In-principle approval has been granted under the letter dated 03/08/2021 and accordingly, administrative approval of the budget based on detailed inspection and investigation was under consideration of the Government.
